New Delhi – Indian Ministry in New Delhi on Wednesday, launched a three-day special campaign to sensitise and mobilise people on measures to prevent and control vector-borne diseases. According to the country’s Health Minister, Harsh Vardhan, the three-day campaign is aimed at making the community a partner for checking vector or mosquito breeding across Delhi. “With a collective effort and active people’s participation, it is easy to ensure that before the monsoon, we make our neighbourhoods and various premises free of mosquitoes,’’ Vardhan said.